The "d" attribute in the "path" element gives instructions for how to draw the figure. 
The commands are listed as follows:
"M 64.00,63.00" - move the pen to the position (64.00,63.00) without drawing anything (uses absolute coordinates);
"L 44.00,63.00" - draw a line from the current position to the position (44.00,63.00);
"L 44.00,50.00" - draw a line from the current position to the position (44.00,50.00);
"L 64.00,50.00" - draw a line from the current position to the position (64.00,50.00);
"L 64.00,45.00" - draw a line from the current position to the position (64.00,45.00);
"L 85.00,57.00" - draw a line from the current position to the position (85.00,57.00);
"L 64.00,68.00" - draw a line from the current position to the position (64.00,68.00);
"L 64.00,63.00" - draw a line from the current position to the position (64.00,63.00) and connect with the beginning of the path.

This results in a straight-sided figure with 7 sides. So, the figure is a heptagon.

(B) heptagon
